def eulerian_path(graph, start, end):
    path = [start]
    current = start
    # For each node, keep track of the edges we have not traversed yet
    used_edges = {node: set() for node in graph}
    
    while current != end or sum(len(graph[node]) - len(used_edges[node]) for node in graph) > 0:
        # Look for an unused edge from the current node
        found = False
        for neighbor, edge_id in graph[current]:
            if (current, neighbor, edge_id) not in used_edges[current]:
                used_edges[current].add((current, neighbor, edge_id))
                used_edges[neighbor].add((current, neighbor, edge_id))
                path.append(neighbor)
                current = neighbor
                found = True
                break
        
        if not found:
            # If we didn't find an unused edge, backtrack to a node that has unused edges
            for i, node in enumerate(path):
                if i > 0 and any((node, neighbor, edge_id) not in used_edges[node] for neighbor, edge_id in graph[node]):
                    # Remove the nodes we've backtracked over
                    backtracked = path[i:]
                    path = path[:i]
                    # Start a new path from this node
                    new_path = eulerian_path(graph, node, current)
                    # Merge the paths
                    path.extend(new_path)
                    path.extend(backtracked)
                    return path
            
            # If we've used all edges, we're done
            break
    
    return path
